iso2god-cli
=========

iso2god-cli is an implementation of Iso2god without GUI.
Use it for convert your Xbox360 iso to GOD files on Windows or Linux.

![screen](http://i.imgur.com/OQ1l61P.png?1)

## Features

- Converts Xbox 360 ISO files to Games on Demand (GOD) format
- Automatic game title lookup via XboxUnity API
- Offline fallback using local CSV databases
- Cross-platform support (Windows/Linux with Mono)

## Requirements

- .NET Framework 2.0 or higher (Windows)
- Mono (Linux)
- Internet connection (optional, for online title lookup)

## Installation

### Compile from source

**Windows:**
```bash
msbuild Iso2God.sln /p:Configuration=Release /p:Platform=x86
```

**Linux:**
```bash
msbuild Iso2God.sln /p:Configuration=Release /p:Platform=x86
```

The compiled executable will be in `bin\Release\Iso2God.exe`

## Usage

```bash
Iso2God.exe <source iso> <destination folder>
```

**Example (Windows):**
```bash
Iso2God.exe "C:\Games\MyGame.iso" "C:\Output\"
```

**Example (Linux with Mono):**
```bash
mono Iso2God.exe "/path/to/game.iso" "/path/to/output/"
```

## Game Title Lookup

The application automatically retrieves game titles using a two-tier system:

1. **Online Lookup**: Uses the [XboxUnity-Scraper](https://github.com/UncreativeXenon/XboxUnity-Scraper) API to fetch game titles
2. **Offline Fallback**: If online lookup fails (no internet connection, timeout, or game not found), it searches local CSV databases:
   - `gamelist_xbox360.csv` - Xbox 360 titles
   - `gamelist_xbox.csv` - Original Xbox titles

The CSV files should be placed in the same directory as the executable.

### CSV Format

**gamelist_xbox360.csv:**
```
title_id	media_id	title_name
584111F1	12345678	Example Game
```

**gamelist_xbox.csv:**
```
title_id	xbe_md5	title_name
4541000D	053432B5...	Example Xbox Game
```

